rman <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]},{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Llewellyn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Welsh: from the personal name <i>Llywelyn</i>, derived from British Celtic <i>Lugubelinos</i>, itself from the divine name <i>Lugus</i> + an uncertain second element often used alone as a name. Through association with <i>llew</i> ‘lion’, it was altered to <i>Llewelyn</i>. This was the name of two princes of north Wales who held the Normans at bay for many years in the 13th century. Etymologically speaking, the form with a fourth <i>-l-</i> is an error, not found as an original Welsh name, but this is now much the most common spelling in the US."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Verch Llywelyn was born in 1239, in Powys, Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Tudyr ap Gronwy of Mathrafarn."},"et":{"1239–":"1239–Surnud","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1239–Female":"1239–Surnud","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","1275":"1275","1240":"1240","about 1275":"umbes 1275","Powys, Wales, United Kingdom":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1239–":"1239–Kuollut","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1239–Female":"1239–Kuollut","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","1275":"1275","1240":"1240","about 1275":"noin 1275","Powys, Wales, United Kingdom":"Powys, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1239–":"1239–Décédée","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1239–Female":"1239–Décédée","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","1275":"1275","1240":"1240","about 1275":"environ 1275","Powys, Wales, United Kingdom":"Powys, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Margaret Verch Llywelyn est née en 1239, à Powys, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Tudyr ap Gronwy of Mathrafarn."},"de":{"1239–":"1239–Verstorben","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1239–Female":"1239–Verstorben","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","1275":"1275","1240":"1240","about 1275":"um 1275","Powys, Wales, United Kingdom":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"Margaret Verch Llywelyn wurde 1239 in Powys, Wales, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Tudyr ap Gronwy of Mathrafarn mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1239–":"1239–Desede","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1239–Female":"1239–Desede","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","1275":"1275","1240":"1240","about 1275":"about 1275"